description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an experienced and motivated Clinical / Health  Psychologist to join our existing Multi-disciplinary team in providing evidence based treatment and support to people experiencing long term pain. CHCP Community Pain Management team provides an extensive service across Hull and the East Riding of Yorkshire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will be contributing Psychological expertise and advice within the service by &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering relevant, effective and sensitive pain management to individuals and groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing, planning and reviewing patients’ pain management treatment appropriately, ensuring that specialist support is focused on the patient’s individual needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Devising and reviewing plans of care aimed at helping patients to achieve their goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promoting patient education and understanding of pain, rehabilitation and self-management strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluation the outcome of care with the multi-disciplinary team, assessing the distress and emotional impact of pain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advising and supporting other members of the MDT in delivering holistic plans of care within a Bio-psychosocial model.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promoting patient self - efficacy in managing long term pain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be supported in delivering this role through individual and group supervision, networking and professional development opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please see Job description for further details .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Further questions should be directed to Kate Cowl &lt;strong&gt;Professional Lead- Kate.cowl@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
